# Frontend Number Formatting

- For money and quantity inputs, use text input with `inputMode="decimal"` instead of `type="number"` for better UX.
- While typing, keep a normalized raw value in state (digits + decimal point), and render it with thousand separators.
- Send numeric values to API without spaces (for empty value send `null` when field is optional).
- In tables/cards, always format numeric amounts with thousand separators.
- Reuse shared helpers from `frontend/src/utils/numberFormat.js`:
  - `sanitizeNumberInput()`
  - `formatNumberInput()`
  - `formatNumberCell()`
  - `numberInputToApi()`
